{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:39:27.684Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Celebrating Initial Success, Adding APIs**\n\nI'm thrilled; the initial testing phase went perfectly! However, my focus has shifted. Now I must integrate billing APIs, and will start again with the requirements. It's time to build v1 invoice/billing APIs under `/api/v1/invoices` or `/api/v1/billing`. The landing page and AI tools will be untouched for now, and no payment provider is needed.\n\n\n**Defining User Roles, Admin Rights**\n\nI'm digging deeper into user roles now, realizing I need to clearly define who can manage invoices. I'm reviewing existing roles like \"gff\\_admin\" and \"client\\_admin\", and I'm deciding if a dedicated \"finance\" role is necessary or if \"gff\\_admin\" will suffice. Also, I need to verify that \"client\\_admin\" can't manage, but can read the invoices that they are allowed to. I'm focusing on securing the API endpoints to match these roles properly.\n\n\n"}}
