s. I want a complete invoice object.\n\n\n**Implementing Invoice ID Logic**\n\nI've got the mock invoice code ready and am confident in its approach to generating unique invoice IDs, which should match the existing GFF style. I've appended the code to `api-auth.ts`, ensuring it aligns with the existing codebase and syntax rules. I'm focusing on the `getNextInvoiceId` function and confirming its proper placement within the module, double-checking its logical flow.\n\n\n**Generating AI Operation IDs**\n\nI've just implemented the `getNextAiOperationId` function, ensuring it generates unique operation IDs. I've integrated this with the mocking data, and now turning my attention to the invoice API models. This will allow for proper management of AI operation IDs and invoice data.\n\n\n**Defining Invoice Object**\n\nI'm now detailing the full structure of the `ApiInvoice` object, including fields such as `status`, `issue_date`, `due_date`, and `category`, along with `hash` and `signature` values. I am also working on the `description` field. I am ensuring that all types are clear and complete.\n\n```typescript\ntype ApiInvoice = {\n  id: string;\n  invoice_number: string;\n  client_id: string;\n  client_name: string;\n  project_id: string;\n  project_name: string;\n  amount: number;\n  currency: string;\n```\n\n\n**Populating Invoice Data**\n\nI'm now populating the invoice data object. I am working through the data for `inv-003`, carefully inputting fields like `client_name`, `project_name`, `amount`, `currency`, and `status`, to ensure they align with the design of the `ApiInvoice` object. The `hash` and `signature` need to be correct. Also, `lastUpdated` timestamp.\n\n\n**Verifying Invoice Objects**\n\nI'm now carefully verifying the invoice objects. I'm focusing on \"inv-003\" and \"inv-004\", paying close attention to their properties: `client_name`, `project_name`, `amount`, `currency`, `status`, `hash`, `signature`, and timestamp. I'm double-checking the descriptions and ensuring data consistency. The process involves comprehensive review.\n\n\n"}}
