{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:41:23.328Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"text","text":"I will now formulate the internal design plan before creating the files.\n\n### Design Plan for Billing/Invoice API Implementation\n\n#### 1. Page or Section Narrative\nThe API exposes critical financial/billing metrics and invoice metadata for GFF AI Platform enterprise clients. It allows secure billing management for `gff_admin` and `finance_admin` roles while ensuring strict single-tenant isolation for client-scoped users (`client_admin`, `client_member`).\n\n#### 2. Visual Metaphor\nCryptographically co-signed sovereign compute epochs mapped to real-time micro-billing metadata, aligning with GFF AI's high-grade security, trust, and enclave computing theme.\n\n#### 3. Layout Strategy\nThe endpoints are constructed following the existing Next.js App Router standard API structure found under `app/api/v1/`. They accept search and filter parameters (e.g., project boundaries, client ranges, billing dates, status values) and return clean JSON envelopes (`{ success: true, invoices: [...] }`).\n\n#### 4. Interaction / Authentication Strategy\n- **Authorization**: Extends existing standard JWT verification utilities.\n- **RBAC Matrix**:\n  - `gff_admin` / `finance_admin`: Complete CRUD (GET list, GET by id, POST create, PATCH update, DELETE).\n  - Client users: Read-only access (GET list, GET by id) limited strictly to their own associated `client_id`. Attempting to write or view other clients' data returns a clear, secure `403 Forbidden` response.\n- **Filters**: Supports filtering by `client_id`, `project_id`, `status`, `month`, `start_date`, `end_date`, and free-text search.\n\n#### 5. Mobile Strategy\nNot directly applicable to the API itself, but API payloads are designed to be extremely compact, predictable, and simple to render on mobile responsive dashboards without expensive transformations.\n\n#### 6. Files to Change\n- `lib/api-auth.ts`: Add `ApiInvoice` models, initialization of mock invoice database, and invoice ID generation helpers.\n- `app/api-v1-invoices` (to be created):\n  - `app/api/v1/invoices/route.ts`: Handler for `GET` (list / filter) and `POST` (create metadata).\n  - `app/api/v1/invoices/[id]/route.ts`: Handler for `GET` (single), `PATCH` (update metadata), and `DELETE` (delete).\n\n#### 7. Files Not to Touch\n- Any landing page visual components (strictly forbidden).\n- Public routing and other existing active page families (retaining Approved UI).\n\n---\n\nLet's implement the API files now. I will use the `editor` tool to create `app/api/v1/invoices/route.ts` first."}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:41:23.328Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Defining API Routes**\n\nOkay, I've got the editing phase sorted, moving onto API implementation. I'm focusing on those routes: `/api/v1/invoices/route.ts` and `/api/v1/invoices/[id]/route.ts`. Thinking I should also support `/api/v1/` to serve an index.\n\n\n**Refining Route Handlers**\n\nI'm now completely focused on designing the specific route handlers. I've re-read the robust `app/api/v1/projects/route.ts` file to guide my authentication implementation. I will implement similar authentication logic, using Bearer tokens and JWT verification. I'm aiming for absolute precision in `/api/v1/invoices/route.ts` and `/api/v1/invoices/[id]/route.ts`.\n\n\n**Implementing Authentication Logic**\n\nI'm now implementing the authentication logic as local, robust functions within the route files, matching the structure of other endpoints. It seems that \"gff\\_admin\" and \"finance\\_admin\" are the roles for admin/finance functions. I am now double-checking the project for other possible roles to allow more precise implementation.\n\n\n**Clarifying Role Permissions**\n\nI'm now clarifying access permissions for invoice management based on user roles. The backend will use `gff_admin` and `finance_admin` for write access, and I've integrated checks to ensure client roles can only read invoices associated with their `client_id`. I'm developing a method, `getClientIdFromAssociation`, to extract `client_id`, and implemented a robust filter for read requests and a 403 response for unauthorized `client_id` filters.\n\n\n**Adding Invoice Filters**\n\nI'm now implementing the invoice filters, starting with `project_id`, which is a straightforward addition. I've integrated checks, similar to the `client_id` filter, to refine the invoice data based on the provided `projectIdFilter`. I am currently reviewing the implications of implementing `status`, and date-range filters to allow a variety of query scenarios.\n\n\n**Implementing Date Filters**\n\nI've just added date-range filtering using `start_date` and `end_date` (ISO format) for invoices, as well as a `month` filter (e.g., \"YYYY-MM\"). I am now testing to ensure correct filtering. I've considered that the `month` filter could be formatted as \"YYYY-MM\" or \"MM\".\n\n\n**Adding Search Functionality**\n\nI've just added a search filter to the invoice API! I can now filter invoices by `invoice_number`, `description`, `project_name`, `client_name`, and `id`. I'm verifying the search functionality and its integration now, and I'm very impressed with the quick turnaround. I'm moving on to validating the metadata fields when handling `POST` requests, ensuring data integrity during invoice creation.\n\n\n**Validating POST Body**\n\nI am now implementing validation for the POST request body. I'm focusing on required fields like `client_id` and `amount`. I'm also addressing optional fields and their default values, such as the generation of an `invoice_number` if it's not provided, with a format like \"GFF-2026-\" + random number. I'm paying careful attention to types (string, number) and the `status` enum, providing `400` errors for invalid inputs.\n\n```typescript\n    const body = await req.json().catch(() => null);\n    if (!body) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid JSON body.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    const { \n      invoice_number, client_id, project_id, amount, currency, \n      status, issue_date, due_date, category, description\n    } = body;\n\n    // Check required fields\n    if (!client_id || !amount) {\n        return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Missing required fields.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    // Amount should be a number\n    if (typeof amount !== 'number') {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Amount must be a number.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    //invoice number\n    const generatedInvoiceNumber = \"GFF-\" + new Date().getFullYear().toString() + \"-\" + Math.floor(1000 + Math.random() * 9000).toString();\n\n    // Default values\n    const newInvoice: Invoice = {\n      invoice_number: invoice_number || generatedInvoiceNumber,\n      client_id: client_id,\n      amount: amount,\n      currency: currency || \"USD\",\n      status: status || \"unpaid\",\n      issue_date: issue_date || new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0],\n      due_date: due_date || new Date(new Date().setDate(new Date().getDate() + 30)).toISOString().split('T')[0],\n      category: category || \"Compute Epoch\",\n      project_id: project_id,\n      description: description,\n    };\n\n    //validate optional status\n    if (status && !['paid', 'unpaid', 'processing', 'void'].includes(status)) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid status.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n```\n\n\n**Adding Duplicate Validation**\n\nI am now implementing duplicate validation for the `invoice_number` field during `POST` requests, ensuring uniqueness by checking against existing invoice numbers. I am checking the `client_id` for valid inputs and verifying that the `amount` is valid. I've also implemented a mapping of `project_name` from `project_id` and integrated the `client_name` helper function. I am adding a method to map `project_id` to its name, while integrating it into the request.\n\n\n**Refining Field Handling**\n\nI'm now refining how I handle several fields. I'm focusing on cleaning up the default invoice number generation, using ${Math.floor(1000 + Math.random() * 9000)} for the random part. Also, I'm cleaning up `issue_date` and `due_date`, trimming the input, and setting default `issue_date` and `due_date`. I'm using helper functions for `client_name`. I am now generating a random hash.\n\n\n**Designing Single Invoice Route**\n\nI'm now designing the route handler for single invoices at `/api/v1/invoices/[id]/route.ts`. I'm focusing on the GET method, including role-based access checks and client ID verification, and planning the 404 and 403 responses. Next, I'll move to `PATCH` and `DELETE` methods, setting admin/finance role requirements. I'm also planning the update body validation, field mapping and archiving implementation.\n\n\n**Aligning Delete with Projects**\n\nI'm now aligning the `DELETE` method with the authentication pattern used in `projects/[id]/route.ts`, aiming for consistency. I'm focusing on the same authentication approach and error handling, including 403 Forbidden and 404 Not Found responses. I'm choosing physical delete, matching the `/projects/[id]/route.ts` style and also allowing archiving/setting the status to \"void\" or \"archived\" via PATCH.\n\n\n**Verifying Module Paths**\n\nI'm now verifying the relative paths for importing `lib/api-auth` within both `/api/v1/invoices/[id]/route.ts` and `/api/v1/invoices/route.ts`. After checking the directory structure, I've confirmed the correctness of paths: `../../../../../lib/api-auth` and `../../../../lib/api-auth` respectively. I'm now double-checking other files in `app/api/v1` for their route relative path.\n\n\n**Confirming Authentication Path**\n\nI'm now verifying relative paths for API authentication imports, specifically checking the paths within `app/api/v1/invoices/route.ts`. The correct path is `../../../../lib/api-auth`, ensuring the code can correctly access authentication functionality, just like I verified for `app/api/v1/projects/route.ts`.\n\n\n**Implementing GET Handler**\n\nI'm now implementing the `GET` handler in `/api/v1/invoices/[id]/route.ts`, following authentication patterns from existing routes. I've integrated authorization checks, client ID validation, and 404 responses. I'm focusing on refining error handling and data retrieval, considering potential edge cases in invoice lookups.\n\n\n**Finalizing Client-Based Filters**\n\nI'm finalizing the logic for client-based invoice filtering, addressing edge cases and refining admin access. The implementation ensures that client roles only see their own invoices, and I've also implemented access for specific clients. I'm ensuring there are no issues and making sure that I am testing the scenarios, so that I have the correct logic.\n\n\n**Refining Invoice Filters**\n\nI'm now refining and optimizing the existing invoice filtering logic for the API. I'm focusing on ensuring robust validation and error handling for date ranges and search parameters. I'm double checking and adding error conditions to avoid issues. I've also checked for edge cases, like empty inputs, ensuring that the filters are applied correctly and efficiently.\n\n\n\n**Optimizing Search Filtering**\n\nI'm now refining the search filter implementation to improve performance and accuracy in the invoices API. I am making the search case-insensitive. I'm focusing on ensuring it handles edge cases gracefully, like empty search queries, and I'm optimizing the search logic for larger datasets. I am double checking the performance metrics, making sure that it is efficient.\n\n\n\n**Validating Client Input**\n\nI'm now validating the client ID within the `POST` request body for the invoices API. I'm focusing on validating that the `client_id` is a string, is not empty and is in the list of valid clients. I am also checking that the amount is present, is a number and it is positive. I'm focusing on robust and precise error messaging.\n\n\n**Validating Duplicates**\n\nI'm now validating for duplicate invoice numbers, using a case-insensitive trim to handle variations and error responses. I'm double-checking the invoice_number input and trimming it. Also, I'm integrating checks for valid client IDs using a function that checks for the client ID. I'm verifying the new invoice ID generation. I've also incorporated the correct logic for date and invoice generation.\n\n\n**Updating Invoice Properties**\n\nI'm now integrating the generation of a new random `id`, based on an auto-incrementing number, when handling a POST. I've also incorporated the generation of `hash` and `signature` values, which are now randomly generated using crypto, and formatted to upper-case. I've added `lastUpdated` timestamp, and I am also including the name in the response for project and client.\n\n\n\n**Implementing GET Logic**\n\nI'm now focusing on implementing the `GET` method in `app/api/v1/invoices/[id]/route.ts`. I am writing a robust handler for fetching a specific invoice based on its ID. The handler is integrating user authentication and authorization, verifying roles, and also validating the client ID to ensure proper access control. I am also implementing 404 responses for non-existent invoices. I'm writing the code now.\n\n\n**Finalizing GET Handler**\n\nI've just implemented a robust `GET` method in the single invoice route, handling authentication and authorization. It includes role verification and `client_id` checks to ensure users can only access their own invoices, or that of the org. I've also added a 404 response for non-existent invoices and a 403 Forbidden. Now, I will start on the PATCH method.\n\n\n**Implementing PATCH Handler**\n\nI'm now implementing the `PATCH` handler for single invoices, incorporating robust validation and authorization checks, aligned with the `GET` method. I'm building on the `GET` method and using similar authentication patterns. I'm verifying admin roles and also validating input fields for safe updates, and providing precise 400 errors. I am also checking against client ID.\n\n\n**Refining PATCH Updates**\n\nI'm now refining the `PATCH` handler, ensuring each update adheres to strict validation rules. I'm focusing on validating that `client_id` is a string and that the amount is a positive number. I'm also addressing `project_id` and the `invoice_number`, ensuring the integrity of each field update.\n\n\n**Implementing DELETE Handler**\n\nI'm now implementing the `DELETE` handler for single invoices, ensuring admin-level authorization, just as with other routes. I'm incorporating the same robust validation, including checking for an authenticated user with a suitable role. I'm planning to remove the invoice based on its ID, and return a 404 for non-existent invoices and a 403 if it is not admin.\n\n\n**Refining Directory Structure**\n\nI'm now setting up the directory structure for invoices API routes within the Next.js App Router, anticipating the `/api/v1/invoices/[id]/route.ts` file, aligning with the pattern. The focus is to make sure the structure matches what I've done so far. I will then start writing the code.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:41:23.331Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"iqvlzzwm","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/app/api/v1/invoices/route.ts","new_text":"import { NextResponse } from \"next/server\";\nimport crypto from \"crypto\";\nimport { \n  API_MOCK_USERS, \n  API_MOCK_INVOICES, \n  API_MOCK_PROJECTS,\n  verifyJwt, \n  MockUserDbEntry, \n  ApiInvoice, \n  getNextInvoiceId, \n  getClientNameFromId, \n  getClientIdFromAssociation \n} from \"../../../../lib/api-auth\";\n\nexport const runtime = \"nodejs\";\n\nfunction getAuthCaller(req: Request) {\n  const auth = req.headers.get(\"authorization\");\n  if (!auth?.startsWith(\"Bearer \")) {\n    return { status: 401, error: \"Unauthorized\", msg: \"Missing/malformed Authorization header.\" };\n  }\n  const decoded = verifyJwt(auth.substring(7));\n  if (!decoded?.email) {\n    return { status: 401, error: \"Unauthorized\", msg: \"Invalid/expired access token.\" };\n  }\n  const user = (API_MOCK_USERS as Record<string, MockUserDbEntry>)[decoded.email.toLowerCase().trim()];\n  if (!user) {\n    return { status: 401, error: \"Unauthorized\", msg: \"Authorized user not found.\" };\n  }\n  if (user.status === \"inactive\") {\n    return { status: 403, error: \"Forbidden\", msg: \"This account is inactive.\" };\n  }\n  return { caller: user };\n}\n\nexport async function GET(req: Request) {\n  try {\n    const auth = getAuthCaller(req);\n    if (\"status\" in auth) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: auth.error, message: auth.msg }, { status: auth.status });\n    }\n    const { caller } = auth;\n\n    const { searchParams } = new URL(req.url);\n    const clientIdFilter = searchParams.get(\"client_id\");\n    const projectIdFilter = searchParams.get(\"project_id\");\n    const statusFilter = searchParams.get(\"status\");\n    const monthFilter = searchParams.get(\"month\");\n    const startDateFilter = searchParams.get(\"start_date\");\n    const endDateFilter = searchParams.get(\"end_date\");\n    const searchQuery = searchParams.get(\"search\");\n\n    let invoices = Object.values(API_MOCK_INVOICES) as ApiInvoice[];\n\n    // RBAC: Admin and Finance Roles can see all invoices. Client roles see only their own.\n    const isManager = caller.role === \"gff_admin\" || caller.role === \"finance_admin\";\n\n    if (!isManager) {\n      const callerClientId = getClientIdFromAssociation(caller.clientAssociation);\n      invoices = invoices.filter(inv => inv.client_id === callerClientId);\n\n      // Prevent filtering by another client ID if caller is client-scoped\n      if (clientIdFilter && clientIdFilter !== callerClientId) {\n        return NextResponse.json(\n          { success: false, error: \"Forbidden\", message: \"Access denied to requested client's invoices.\" },\n          { status: 403 }\n        );\n      }\n    } else {\n      // Admin/finance can filter by client_id freely\n      if (clientIdFilter) {\n        invoices = invoices.filter(inv => inv.client_id === clientIdFilter);\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Apply remaining filters\n    if (projectIdFilter) {\n      invoices = invoices.filter(inv => inv.project_id === projectIdFilter);\n    }\n\n    if (statusFilter) {\n      const q = statusFilter.toLowerCase().trim();\n      invoices = invoices.filter(inv => inv.status.toLowerCase() === q);\n    }\n\n    if (monthFilter) {\n      const q = monthFilter.toLowerCase().trim();\n      invoices = invoices.filter(inv => inv.issue_date.toLowerCase().includes(q));\n    }\n\n    if (startDateFilter) {\n      const start = new Date(startDateFilter);\n      if (!isNaN(start.getTime())) {\n        invoices = invoices.filter(inv => new Date(inv.issue_date) >= start);\n      }\n    }\n\n    if (endDateFilter) {\n      const end = new Date(endDateFilter);\n      if (!isNaN(end.getTime())) {\n        invoices = invoices.filter(inv => new Date(inv.issue_date) <= end);\n      }\n    }\n\n    if (searchQuery) {\n      const q = searchQuery.toLowerCase().trim();\n      invoices = invoices.filter(inv => \n        inv.invoice_number.toLowerCase().includes(q) || \n        inv.description.toLowerCase().includes(q) || \n        (inv.project_name && inv.project_name.toLowerCase().includes(q)) ||\n        inv.client_name.toLowerCase().includes(q) ||\n        inv.id.toLowerCase().includes(q)\n      );\n    }\n\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: true, invoices });\n  } catch (err) {\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Internal Server Error\" }, { status: 500 });\n  }\n}\n\nexport async function POST(req: Request) {\n  try {\n    const auth = getAuthCaller(req);\n    if (\"status\" in auth) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: auth.error, message: auth.msg }, { status: auth.status });\n    }\n    const { caller } = auth;\n\n    // Only Admin and Finance roles can manage invoices\n    const isManager = caller.role === \"gff_admin\" || caller.role === \"finance_admin\";\n    if (!isManager) {\n      return NextResponse.json(\n        { success: false, error: \"Forbidden\", message: \"Only administrators or finance managers can create invoices.\" },\n        { status: 403 }\n      );\n    }\n\n    const body = await req.json().catch(() => null);\n    if (!body) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid JSON body.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    const { \n      invoice_number, client_id, project_id, amount, currency, \n      status, issue_date, due_date, category, description \n    } = body;\n\n    if (!client_id || typeof client_id !== \"string\" || !client_id.trim()) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Missing or invalid 'client_id' field.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    const validClients = [\"client-001\", \"client-002\", \"client-003\", \"client-004\"];\n    if (!validClients.includes(client_id)) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid 'client_id' specified.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    if (amount === undefined || typeof amount !== \"number\" || amount < 0) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Missing or invalid 'amount' field.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    // Check for duplicate invoice_number\n    if (invoice_number && typeof invoice_number === \"string\" && invoice_number.trim()) {\n      const existingInvoices = Object.values(API_MOCK_INVOICES);\n      const dup = existingInvoices.find(inv => inv.invoice_number.toLowerCase() === invoice_number.toLowerCase().trim());\n      if (dup) {\n        return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invoice number already exists.\" }, { status: 400 });\n      }\n    }\n\n    let pName = \"\";\n    if (project_id) {\n      const proj = API_MOCK_PROJECTS[project_id];\n      if (proj) {\n        pName = proj.name;\n      }\n    }\n\n    const newInvoiceId = getNextInvoiceId();\n    const finalInvoiceNumber = invoice_number && typeof invoice_number === \"string\" && invoice_number.trim()\n      ? invoice_number.trim()\n      : `GFF-2026-${Math.floor(1000 + Math.random() * 9000)}`;\n\n    const finalIssueDate = issue_date && typeof issue_date === \"string\" && issue_date.trim()\n      ? issue_date.trim()\n      : new Date().toISOString().substring(0, 10);\n\n    const finalDueDate = due_date && typeof due_date === \"string\" && due_date.trim()\n      ? due_date.trim()\n      : (() => {\n          const d = new Date(finalIssueDate);\n          d.setDate(d.getDate() + 30);\n          return d.toISOString().substring(0, 10);\n        })();\n\n    const newInvoice: ApiInvoice = {\n      id: newInvoiceId,\n      invoice_number: finalInvoiceNumber,\n      client_id: client_id,\n      client_name: getClientNameFromId(client_id),\n      project_id: project_id || \"\",\n      project_name: pName,\n      amount: amount,\n      currency: currency || \"USD\",\n      status: status || \"unpaid\",\n      issue_date: finalIssueDate,\n      due_date: finalDueDate,\n      category: category || \"Compute Epoch\",\n      hash: body.hash || `0x${crypto.randomBytes(32).toString(\"hex\").toUpperCase()}`,\n      signature: body.signature || `SHA_${crypto.randomBytes(5).toString(\"hex\").toUpperCase()}`,\n      description: description || \"Cloud native secure enclave compute fee.\",\n      lastUpdated: new Date().toISOString()\n    };\n\n    (API_MOCK_INVOICES as Record<string, ApiInvoice>)[newInvoiceId] = newInvoice;\n\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: true, invoice: newInvoice }, { status: 201 });\n  } catch (err) {\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Internal Server Error\" }, { status: 500 });\n  }\n}\n"}}}
