ously checking the `invoice_number`, `client_id`, `project_id`, `amount`, `currency`, `status`, `issue_date`, `due_date`, `category`, and `description` fields. I'm prioritizing data type validation, required fields, and acceptable values for each field, particularly for client ID.\n\n\n**Validating Input Parameters**\n\nI am now meticulously verifying input parameters, specifically focusing on `amount` and `invoice_number`. I've added robust checks for duplicate invoice numbers, using a case-insensitive comparison to improve robustness. I'm focusing on handling both missing values and invalid values gracefully, returning informative error messages when needed. My focus is on producing more descriptive errors.\n\n\n"}}
