{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:42:43.021Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Creating the Endpoint**\n\nI've successfully created the `app/api/v1/invoices/route.ts` file. My next objective is the implementation of `app/api/v1/invoices/[id]/route.ts`. I intend to draft a similarly concise version, aiming to stay well under 6000 characters.\n\n\n**Designing the GET Request**\n\nI'm now designing the GET request handler for fetching individual invoice details. My plan is to first authenticate the caller, then retrieve the invoice by its ID. I'm focusing on error handling and returning appropriate status codes and responses for unauthorized access or non-existent invoices. I'm leveraging mock data structures to simulate the API response.\n\n\n**Implementing PATCH Endpoint**\n\nI've completed the PATCH endpoint for invoice updates. I added authentication and authorization checks, ensuring only managers can modify invoices. I retrieve the invoice by ID and simulate a response if the invoice is found. I'm focusing on handling unauthorized attempts and providing appropriate error codes, ensuring proper security protocols are in place for the API.\n\n\n**Validating Incoming Data**\n\nI'm now implementing robust data validation for the update endpoint to prevent bad requests. I've added checks to ensure the body exists and that all required fields are present. I'm focusing on validating the data types and specific values for keys like `client_id` and `amount`. I will ensure that the validation process covers a diverse range of potential issues. I am using the standard error responses.\n\n\n**Refining Input Validation**\n\nI'm currently focused on refining the input validation logic within my code. I've integrated specific checks for the `amount`, `project_id`, and `invoice_number` fields within the PATCH endpoint. My goal is to ensure data integrity. I am now checking for things like valid amounts, non-empty invoice numbers, and ensuring invoice numbers are unique. I am aiming to respond with appropriate error messages to inform the user of validation failures.\n\n\n**Finalizing the DELETE Endpoint**\n\nI've completed the DELETE endpoint. I've added authentication and authorization, ensuring only managers can delete invoices. I retrieve the invoice by its ID. If the invoice exists, I remove it from the mock data and return a success response; otherwise, a 'Not Found' error. I am returning appropriate status codes.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:42:43.024Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"ua995uef","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/app/api/v1/invoices/[id]/route.ts","new_text":"import { NextResponse } from \"next/server\";\nimport { \n  API_MOCK_USERS, API_MOCK_INVOICES, verifyJwt, \n  MockUserDbEntry, ApiInvoice, getClientIdFromAssociation, getClientNameFromId, API_MOCK_PROJECTS\n} from \"../../../../../lib/api-auth\";\n\nexport const runtime = \"nodejs\";\n\nfunction getAuthCaller(req: Request) {\n  const auth = req.headers.get(\"authorization\");\n  if (!auth?.startsWith(\"Bearer \")) return null;\n  const decoded = verifyJwt(auth.substring(7));\n  if (!decoded?.email) return null;\n  const user = (API_MOCK_USERS as Record<string, MockUserDbEntry>)[decoded.email.toLowerCase().trim()];\n  return user && user.status !== \"inactive\" ? user : null;\n}\n\nexport async function GET(req: Request, { params }: { params: any }) {\n  try {\n    const caller = getAuthCaller(req);\n    if (!caller) return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Unauthorized\" }, { status: 401 });\n    const { id } = await params;\n    const invoice = (API_MOCK_INVOICES as Record<string, ApiInvoice>)[id];\n    if (!invoice) return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Not Found\" }, { status: 404 });\n\n    const isMgr = caller.role === \"gff_admin\" || caller.role === \"finance_admin\";\n    if (!isMgr) {\n      const cid = getClientIdFromAssociation(caller.clientAssociation);\n      if (invoice.client_id !== cid) return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Forbidden\" }, { status: 403 });\n    }\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: true, invoice });\n  } catch (err) {\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Internal Server Error\" }, { status: 500 });\n  }\n}\n\nexport async function PATCH(req: Request, { params }: { params: any }) {\n  try {\n    const caller = getAuthCaller(req);\n    if (!caller) return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Unauthorized\" }, { status: 401 });\n    const isMgr = caller.role === \"gff_admin\" || caller.role === \"finance_admin\";\n    if (!isMgr) return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Forbidden\" }, { status: 403 });\n\n    const { id } = await params;\n    const invoice = (API_MOCK_INVOICES as Record<string, ApiInvoice>)[id];\n    if (!invoice) return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Not Found\" }, { status: 404 });\n\n    const body = await req.json().catch(() => null);\n    if (!body) return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\" }, { status: 400 });\n\n    const fields = [\n      \"invoice_number\", \"client_id\", \"project_id\", \"amount\", \n      \"currency\", \"status\", \"issue_date\", \"due_date\", \n      \"category\", \"description\", \"hash\", \"signature\"\n    ];\n\n    for (const key of fields) {\n      if (body[key] !== undefined) {\n        if (key === \"client_id\") {\n          const valids = [\"client-001\", \"client-002\", \"client-003\", \"client-004\"];\n          if (!valids.includes(body.client_id)) {\n            return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid client_id\" }, { status: 400 });\n          }\n          invoice.client_id = body.client_id;\n          invoice.client_name = getClientNameFromId(body.client_id);\n        } else if (key === \"amount\") {\n          if (typeof body.amount !== \"number\" || body.amount < 0) {\n            return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid amount\" }, { status: 400 });\n          }\n          invoice.amount = body.amount;\n        } else if (key === \"project_id\") {\n          invoice.project_id = body.project_id;\n          invoice.project_name = body.project_id ? (API_MOCK_PROJECTS[body.project_id]?.name || \"\") : \"\";\n        } else if (key === \"invoice_number\") {\n          if (typeof body.invoice_number !== \"string\" || !body.invoice_number.trim()) {\n            return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid invoice_number\" }, { status: 400 });\n          }\n          const otherInvs = Object.values(API_MOCK_INVOICES).filter(inv => inv.id !== id);\n          if (otherInvs.some(inv => inv.invoice_number.toLowerCase() === body.invoice_number.toLowerCase().trim())) {\n            return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invoice number already exists\" }, { status: 400 });\n          }\n          invoice.invoice_number = body.invoice_number.trim();\n        } else {\n          (invoice as any)[key] = typeof body[key] === \"string\" ? body[key].trim() : body[key];\n        }\n      }\n    }\n\n    invoice.lastUpdated = new Date().toISOString();\n    (API_MOCK_INVOICES as Record<string, ApiInvoice>)[id] = invoice;\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: true, invoice });\n  } catch (err) {\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Internal Server Error\" }, { status: 500 });\n  }\n}\n\nexport async function DELETE(req: Request, { params }: { params: any }) {\n  try {\n    const caller = getAuthCaller(req);\n    if (!caller) return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Unauthorized\" }, { status: 401 });\n    const isMgr = caller.role === \"gff_admin\" || caller.role === \"finance_admin\";\n    if (!isMgr) return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Forbidden\" }, { status: 403 });\n\n    const { id } = await params;\n    if (!(API_MOCK_INVOICES as Record<string, ApiInvoice>)[id]) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Not Found\" }, { status: 404 });\n    }\n    delete (API_MOCK_INVOICES as Record<string, ApiInvoice>)[id];\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: true, message: \"Invoice deleted.\" });\n  } catch (err) {\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Internal Server Error\" }, { status: 500 });\n  }\n}"}}}
