{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:43:10.468Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Verifying API Functionality**\n\nI've successfully created the necessary files. My current focus is crafting a script to thoroughly test the invoice and billing APIs. The goal is to mirror the format of existing test scripts, specifically `scripts/test-project-apis.js` and `scripts/test-ai-operations-apis.js`, to ensure flawless operation and security adherence. I'm prioritizing comprehensive testing of API endpoints and associated constraints.\n\n\n**Modeling Test Cases**\n\nI'm now focused on modeling the test file as `scripts/test-invoice-apis.js`. I've outlined the compilation and handler requirements. I'm exploring test cases involving different auth tokens, including those with `gff_admin`, `client_admin`, and `client_member` roles. I've realized the need to test the `finance_admin` role. I'm considering how to incorporate a mock user with the `finance_admin` role, either by adding it to `DEFAULT_API_MOCK_USERS` or through a dynamic approach.\n\n\n**Refining Role-Based Testing**\n\nI'm now refining the testing strategy for role-based access. I'm leaning toward combining approaches: testing with both dynamically edited user roles *and* a mock finance user. This will provide broad coverage for the `finance_admin`, `gff_admin`, and `client_admin` roles. I'm actively writing the test script, ensuring it mirrors the structure of existing scripts and produces clean, successful output. I'm focusing on handling both read and management permissions correctly. The foundational structure of `scripts/test-invoice-apis.js` is set.\n\n\n**Testing API Authentication**\n\nI've completed the initial structure of `test-invoice-apis.js`. I'm now verifying the authentication guards using `gff_admin`, `client_admin`, and `client_member` roles. I'm testing access to the invoice route with different auth tokens, specifically for `GET` requests, using the pre-defined mock users. This includes checking behavior for inactive accounts. I'm ensuring all calls are well-formed and secure.\n\n\n**Validating Security Protocols**\n\nI'm now integrating detailed authentication tests into the `test-invoice-apis.js` script. I'm focusing on validating expected responses for inactive users (403), no tokens (401), and different roles, specifically `gff_admin` and `client_admin`. I'm verifying the admin can see all invoices, while the client is restricted to their own. I'm ensuring robust security measures are in place to prevent data leakage.\n\n\n**Implementing Filtering Logic**\n\nI'm now focusing on implementing and testing the filtering logic for the invoice API. I'm verifying that the cross-tenant filters correctly return a 403 error for unauthorized access. Also, I'm validating that the admin can properly filter invoices by client ID and search terms, ensuring the results are accurate and secure. I am focusing on ensuring that the filter works with search terms such as `Retail` and client ID `client-003`.\n\n\n**Testing Date Range**\n\nI'm now integrating date range filters, validating correct date-based results. The script verifies successful range-based queries and error handling. I'm focusing on ensuring accurate invoice retrieval within the specified date parameters. I'm testing the ability to fetch a single invoice, as well.\n\n\n**Verifying PATCH Operations**\n\nI'm now incorporating tests for the PATCH operation within the invoice API, including updates by both client and admin roles. I'm verifying the expected 403 error for client attempts and a 200/201 (success) response for admins. I'm focusing on the successful update, and the verification of correct client name mapping.\n\n\n**Validating DELETE Operations**\n\nI'm now writing tests for DELETE operations, focusing on robust role-based access control. I'm verifying the expected 403 error for client attempts and a 204 (no content) response for admin users. This ensures secure invoice deletion practices.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:43:10.470Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"o42rx0rg","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/scripts/test-invoice-apis.js","new_text":"/* eslint-disable */\n\nconst { execSync } = require('child_process');\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst path = require('path');\nconst T = path.join(__dirname, '..', 'temp-invoice-build');\nif (fs.existsSync(T)) fs.rmSync(T, { recursive: true, force: true });\ntry {\n  execSync('npx tsc lib/api-auth.ts app/api/v1/invoices/route.ts app/api/v1/invoices/[id]/route.ts --outDir temp-invoice-build --module commonjs --target es2022 --moduleResolution node --esModuleInterop --skipLibCheck', { stdio: 'ignore' });\n  console.log(\"✔ Compile success.\");\n} catch (e) {\n  process.exit(1);\n}\nconst apiAuth = require('../temp-invoice-build/lib/api-auth.js');\nconst invRoute = require('../temp-invoice-build/app/api/v1/invoices/route.js');\nconst invIdRoute = require('../temp-invoice-build/app/api/v1/invoices/[id]/route.js');\n\nfunction getAuth(email) {\n  const u = apiAuth.API_MOCK_USERS[email];\n  return `Bearer ${apiAuth.signJwt({ sub: u.id, email: u.email, role: u.role, name: u.name, clientAssociation: u.clientAssociation })}`;\n}\n\nasync function run() {\n  try {\n    const admin = getAuth(\"s.vance@governance.gff.ai\"); // gff_admin\n    const client = getAuth(\"a.mercer@apex-sovereign.gff.ai\"); // client_admin (client-001)\n    const member = getAuth(\"s.jenkins@fed-treasury.gff.ai\"); // client_member (client-004)\n    const inactive = getAuth(\"m.vance@sovereign-logistics.gff.ai\"); // inactive\n\n    // 1. Auth guards\n    let res = await invRoute.GET(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/invoices\", { headers: { \"Authorization\": inactive } }));\n    if (res.status !== 403) throw new Error(\"Inactive user must be 403\");\n    res = await invRoute.GET(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/invoices\"));\n    if (res.status !== 401) throw new Error(\"No token must be 401\");\n\n    // 2. GET list for Admin (should see all invoices)\n    res = await invRoute.GET(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/invoices\", { headers: { \"Authorization\": admin } }));\n    let d = await res.json();\n    if (res.status !== 200 || d.invoices.length < 4) throw new Error(\"Admin list failed\");\n\n    // 3. GET list for Client (should see only client-001)\n    res = await invRoute.GET(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/invoices\", { headers: { \"Authorization\": client } }));\n    d = await res.json();\n    if (res.status !== 200) throw new Error(\"Client list failed\");\n    if (d.invoices.some(i => i.client_id !== \"client-001\")) throw new Error(\"Client list leakage\");\n\n    // 4. Client filter cross-tenant boundary check\n    res = await invRoute.GET(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/invoices?client_id=client-003\", { headers: { \"Authorization\": client } }));\n    if (res.status !== 403) throw new Error(\"Cross-tenant filter must be 403\");\n\n    // 5. Admin filtering (search and client_id)\n    res = await invRoute.GET(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/invoices?client_id=client-003\", { headers: { \"Authorization\": admin } }));\n    d = await res.json();\n    if (d.invoices.some(i => i.client_id !== \"client-003\")) throw new Error(\"Admin client_id filter failed\");\n\n    res = await invRoute.GET(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/invoices?search=Retail\", { headers: { \"Authorization\": admin } }));\n    d = await res.json();\n    if (d.invoices.length !== 1 || !d.invoices[0].project_name.includes(\"Sovereign\") && !d.invoices[0].project_name.includes(\"Consensus\")) {\n      if (!d.invoices[0].client_name.includes(\"Apex\") && !d.invoices[0].client_name.includes(\"Retail\")) {\n        throw new Error(\"Search filter failed\");\n      }\n    }\n\n    // 6. Date Range Filters\n    res = await invRoute.GET(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/invoices?start_date=2026-06-10&end_date=2026-06-26\", { headers: { \"Authorization\": admin } }));\n    d = await res.json();\n    if (d.invoices.some(i => i.issue_date < \"2026-06-10\" || i.issue_date > \"2026-06-26\")) throw new Error(\"Date range filter failed\");\n\n    // 7. GET Single invoice\n    res = await invIdRoute.GET(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/invoices/inv-001\", { headers: { \"Authorization\": admin } }), { params: Promise.resolve({ id: \"inv-001\" }) });\n    d = await res.json();\n    if (res.status !== 200 || d.invoice.id !== \"inv-001\") throw new Error(\"GET single invoice failed\");\n\n    res = await invIdRoute.GET(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/invoices/inv-002\", { headers: { \"Authorization\": client } }), { params: Promise.resolve({ id: \"inv-002\" }) });\n    if (res.status !== 403) throw new Error(\"Cross-tenant GET single must be 403\");\n\n    // 8. POST create invoice (Unauthorized for client, Allowed for Admin)\n    const invData = { invoice_number: \"GFF-2026-TEST\", client_id: \"client-002\", amount: 1500.00, category: \"Compute SLA\" };\n    res = await invRoute.POST(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/invoices\", { method: \"POST\", headers: { \"Authorization\": client }, body: JSON.stringify(invData) }));\n    if (res.status !== 403) throw new Error(\"Client POST must be 403\");\n\n    res = await invRoute.POST(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/invoices\", { method: \"POST\", headers: { \"Authorization\": admin }, body: JSON.stringify(invData) }));\n    if (res.status !== 201) throw new Error(\"Admin POST failed\");\n    d = await res.json();\n    const createdId = d.invoice.id;\n    if (d.invoice.client_name !== \"Global Retail Enclave [Preview Client]\") throw new Error(\"Post client name mapping failed\");\n\n    // 9. PATCH update invoice\n    res = await invIdRoute.PATCH(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/invoices/\" + createdId, { method: \"PATCH\", headers: { \"Authorization\": client }, body: JSON.stringify({ amount: 9999 }) }), { params: Promise.resolve({ id: createdId }) });\n    if (res.status !== 403) throw new Error(\"Client PATCH must be 403\");\n\n    res = await invIdRoute.PATCH(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/invoices/\" + createdId, { method: \"PATCH\", headers: { \"Authorization\": admin }, body: JSON.stringify({ amount: 5000, description: \"Updated SLA\" }) }), { params: Promise.resolve({ id: createdId }) });\n    if (res.status !== 200) throw new Error(\"Admin PATCH failed\");\n    d = await res.json();\n    if (d.invoice.amount !== 5000 || d.invoice.description !== \"Updated SLA\") throw new Error(\"PATCH field updates failed\");\n\n    // 10. DELETE invoice\n    res = await invIdRoute.DELETE(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/invoices/\" + createdId, { method: \"DELETE\", headers: { \"Authorization\": client } }), { params: Promise.resolve({ id: createdId }) });\n    if (res.status !== 403) throw new Error(\"Client DELETE must be 403\");\n\n    res = await invIdRoute.DELETE(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/invoices/\" + createdId, { method: \"DELETE\", headers: { \"Authorization\": admin } }), { params: Promise.resolve({ id: createdId }) });\n    if (res.status !== 200) throw new Error(\"Admin DELETE failed\");\n\n    res = await invIdRoute.GET(new Request(\"http://l/api/v1/invoices/\" + createdId, { headers: { \"Authorization\": admin } }), { params: Promise.resolve({ id: createdId }) });\n    if (res.status !== 404) throw new Error(\"Lookup of deleted invoice must be 404\");\n\n    console.log(\"\\x1b[32m✔ VERIFICATION SUCCESSFUL: Invoices CRUD APIs Verified!\\x1b[0m\");\n    process.exit(0);\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.error(\"\\x1b[31m✖ Test failed:\\x1b[0m\", err.stack || err.message);\n    process.exit(1);\n  } finally {\n    if (fs.existsSync(T)) fs.rmSync(T, { recursive: true, force: true });\n  }\n}\nrun();"}}}
