{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:46:57.800Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"sf1lfzcs","input":{"summary":"Implemented high-quality MVP Billing & Invoice Metadata APIs under `/api/v1/invoices` and `/api/v1/invoices/[id]` following strict tenant isolation, enterprise RBAC security, and input validations.\n\n### Summary of Changes:\n1. **Model & Mock DB Setup (`lib/api-auth.ts`)**:\n   - Defined the robust `ApiInvoice` metadata model interface with attributes like `id`, `invoice_number`, `client_id`, `client_name`, `project_id`, `project_name`, `amount`, `currency`, `status`, `issue_date`, `due_date`, `category`, `hash`, `signature`, `description`, and `lastUpdated`.\n   - Seeded 4 initial mock invoices aligned with the dashboard data to ensure visual consistency.\n   - Initialized global persistence `(global as any)._apiMockInvoices` and created the `getNextInvoiceId()` generator helper.\n\n2. **Endpoints Implementation**:\n   - **`app/api/v1/invoices/route.ts`**:\n     - **`GET`**: Lists invoices. Supports filters for `client_id`, `project_id`, `status`, `month`, `start_date`, `end_date`, and generic `search` query. Enforces RBAC boundary checks: Client roles only view their own invoices, while Admin (`gff_admin`) and Finance (`finance_admin`) can view and filter across all clients.\n     - **`POST`**: Creates invoice metadata. Restricted to Admin/Finance roles. Includes strict request body checks, client-id sanity validation, and duplicates protection.\n   - **`app/api/v1/invoices/[id]/route.ts`**:\n     - **`GET`**: Retrieves a single invoice, with client boundaries secured.\n     - **`PATCH`**: Updates invoice metadata. Restricted to Admin/Finance roles.\n     - **`DELETE`**: Deletes the invoice. Restricted to Admin/Finance roles.\n\n3. **Validation Suite & Verification**:\n   - Created `scripts/test-invoice-apis.js` to automatically verify compiling, token verification, route routing, filtering parameters, role-based boundaries, invoice creation, invoice updates, and deletion.\n   - Successfully ran the entire validation suite with 100% test success. Checked that the workspace is fully compliant with ESLint rules.","verified":true}}}
